   "source": [
    "# Exploring the PiSequence Project\n",
    "\n",
    "This Jupyter notebook provides an interactive exploration of the **PiSequence** project, a tool designed to investigate the decimal expansion of π (pi) and the hypothesis that π is a normal number. The project allows users to generate π’s decimals, search for specific sequences, analyze digit frequencies, explore meaningful sequences, and interact with the results via a web interface.\n",
    "\n",
    "## What You'll Learn\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we will:\n",
    "- Generate the decimal expansion of π and save it to a file.\n",
    "- Search for specific sequences within π’s decimals.\n",
    "- Analyze the frequency of digits (0 to 9) and visualize the results with a histogram.\n",
    "- Search for meaningful sequences, such as prime numbers, a birth date, and a binary-encoded message.\n",
    "- Run unit tests to validate the sequence search functionality.\n",
    "- Explore test sequences provided in a file.\n",
    "- Use a web interface to interactively search for sequences and view digit frequencies.\n",
    "- Discuss the philosophical implications of π’s normality hypothesis.\n",
    "\n",
    "## About This Project\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is part of the **PiSequence** project, which includes:\n",
    "- Python scripts for generating and analyzing π’s decimals (`src/`).\n",
    "- Data files storing π’s decimals and test sequences (`data/`).\n",
    "- Visualizations of digit frequencies (`visualizations/`).\n",
    "- Documentation on the normality hypothesis (`docs/`).\n",
    "- Unit tests to validate functionality (`tests/`).\n",
    "- An interactive web interface (`web/`).\n",
    "\n",
    "Check out the full project on [GitHub](https://github.com/muerfi/PiSequence).\n",
    "\n",
    "Let’s dive in!"
   ]
